transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, I tried to place an order on my phone, and I just wanted to know if that went through or not.

Speaker 1: Okay. Is this the number that you tried to place the order with?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: 108-507-5348?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: No, I'm not seeing anything showing up under that number, actually.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I'll tell you what I can do for you.

Speaker 2: Why don't you just go ahead and – did you put your e-mail address in?

Speaker 1: Yes, they already had all that information automatically when I was – yeah.

Speaker 2: Well, let me try to look for it on your e-mail.

Speaker 1: That's what I'm saying, because nothing is coming up under your phone number at all.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Do you have something out there?

Speaker 2: My e-mail –

Speaker 1: Yes, please.

Speaker 2: Vincent, with an E in the end, VincenteGrande, G-R-A-N-D-E, at AOL.com.

Speaker 1: Give me one second.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Quite a few things came up under that e-mail.

Speaker 2: I don't know why.

Speaker 1: I have Vincent's e-mail.

Speaker 2: It's V-I-C-E-N-T-A-G-R –

Speaker 1: V-I-N.

Speaker 2: V-I-N-C-E-N-T-E.

Speaker 1: V-I-N-C-E-N-T-A-G-R-A-N-D-E, at AOL.com.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Let me try that one more time.

Speaker 2: Okay, Vincent.

Speaker 1: I was able to pull you up here.

Speaker 2: It looks like that – I do see an order that was placed, and it's currently at the pharmacy.

Speaker 1: It looks like that you – yeah, it looks like it was done today.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I did.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah.

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so it was done.

Speaker 2: Well, and what exactly did you purchase?

Speaker 1: It looks like that you got the Viagra, 100 milligrams, and you got 20, and then you – yeah, you got 10,

Speaker 2: and then you upgraded to the extra 10 for a total of 20.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Right?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: And what kind of delivery are we looking at?

Speaker 1: Well, it's at the pharmacy right now.

Speaker 2: They're going to – the pharmacy usually goes through your medical survey.

Speaker 1: If everything goes fine with your medical survey,

Speaker 2: it usually takes about seven to ten business days from the date of your order shipped out.

Speaker 1: It usually comes a lot faster, but for some reason, like last week,

Speaker 2: the weather's been messing up a lot of places,

Speaker 1: so we've been told to put out that date until things kind of clear up across this country, you know,

Speaker 2: because it's dealing with the United States Postal Service.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Not a problem.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Take care.
